  "signature": "ed25519:b1c2d3e4f5a6b7c8d9e0f1a2b3c4d5e6f7a8b9c0d1e2f3a4b5c6d7e8f9a0b1c2",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-mrl2-documented-procedures",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022 R2 is a commercially validated CFD solver with documented V&V procedures, ISO 9001 quality management certification, and version-controlled release notes. All simulation scripts were managed under Git version control with tagged releases. Software qualification records confirm the solver meets MRL 2 requirements for hemolysis prediction applications."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-mrl2-benchmarks",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification was performed using standard benchmark cases including lid-driven cavity flow (Re=1000) and Poiseuille flow, achieving agreement within 0.5% of analytical solutions. The hemolysis power-law model implementation was verified against published reference solutions from Giersiepen et al. All benchmark results are archived in the project verification report VR-2023-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-gci-less-5pct",
      "rationale": "Grid convergence study performed on three systematically refined meshes (2.1M, 6.8M, 18.4M elements) following the GCI method per Celik et al. (2008). The fine-grid GCI for the hemolysis index was 2.3%, well below the 5% acceptance threshold. The production mesh of 6.8M polyhedral elements was selected as the converged mesh balancing accuracy and computational cost. Temporal convergence was confirmed with residuals below 1e-5 for all equations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-boundary-match",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions for the hemolysis validation study were conducted at 37°C using bovine blood with hematocrit 33±2%, matching the simulation boundary conditions. Flow rates of 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 L/min at 2500 RPM were tested, spanning the clinical CPB operating envelope. Inlet and outlet pressure boundary conditions were derived from the experimental setup with documented uncertainty of ±2 mmHg."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-rh-index",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest, the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH), was compared between CFD predictions and experimental measurements across all 5 operating points. The mean absolute percentage error was 8.7% across all conditions, within the accepted tolerance of 15% for MRL 2 hemolysis assessments. Systematic bias was less than 5% across the operating envelope, confirming adequate predictive capability."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-hemolysis-index",
      "rationale": "The NIH and RH index are the regulatory-standard quantities of interest for hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance on blood-contacting devices. These quantities directly map to the clinical decision criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device). The CFD-derived shear stress exposure integral used to compute NIH is a well-established surrogate for erythrocyte damage in rotary blood pumps, as confirmed by published literature."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-cpb-envelope",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were conducted using the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under flow conditions spanning the intended CPB clinical operating envelope. The validation geometry is geometrically similar to the device under assessment with the same impeller topology. Operating conditions (flow rate 2–6 L/min, speed 2000–3000 RPM) encompass the worst-case hemolysis conditions identified in the sensitivity study, ensuring the validation domain is relevant to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-scoped-out-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, separate characterization of numerical solver error beyond the GCI-based discretization error assessment is not required. The commercial solver's iterative convergence was monitored and confirmed with residuals below 1e-5 for all transport equations, and mass imbalance below 0.01%. Solver error is subsumed within the discretization error assessment and the code verification activities already performed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-scoped-out-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal use error assessment is not required. Analyst qualifications were documented: the lead analyst holds a PhD in computational fluid dynamics with 8 years of experience in blood pump simulation. Simulation setup was independently reviewed by a second qualified analyst. Standard operating procedures for CFD setup and post-processing were followed and documented in the project quality plan QP-2023-CPB."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-scoped-out-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal model form uncertainty quantification is not required. The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on its established performance for rotary blood pump flows as documented in the literature. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model is the industry-standard approach for CFD hemolysis prediction. Model form adequacy is supported by the output comparison results demonstrating agreement within acceptance criteria."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-scoped-out-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, comprehensive model input uncertainty propagation is not required. Key model inputs including blood viscosity (3.5 mPa·s), density (1060 kg/m³), and hematocrit (33%) are well-characterized physiological values with documented sources. Geometric inputs were derived from FDA-published CAD files with dimensional tolerances of ±0.05 mm. Boundary conditions were derived from experimental measurements with documented uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-scoped-out-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, detailed characterization of test sample variability is not required. Experimental validation used fresh bovine blood from a single lot with hematocrit adjusted to 33±2% and documented plasma-free hemoglobin baseline below 20 mg/dL. Sample preparation followed ASTM F1841 standard practice. Inter-batch variability was not systematically characterized, which is acceptable at MRL 2 given the medium model influence classification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/equivalency-scoped-out-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, formal equivalency mapping between simulation inputs and experimental parameters is not required. The simulation boundary conditions were set to match experimental values as closely as possible, with deviations documented in the validation report. Flow rate boundary conditions matched experimental values within ±2%, and rotational speed was specified exactly. These minor deviations are within the uncertainty of the experimental measurements themselves."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-mrl2-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for the CFD hemolysis prediction model under CPB conditions is accepted at Medium assurance level for MRL 2. All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels: software quality assurance (2/2), numerical code verification (2/2), discretization error (3/2, exceeding requirement), test conditions (2/2), output comparison (2/2), relevance of QOI (2/2), and relevance of validation activities (2/2). Six factors were appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 with documented rationale consistent with ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3 requirements for Medium model influence and High decision consequence. The primary acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device) was met across all five worst-case operating points with mean prediction error of 8.7%, within the 15% tolerance. Grid convergence was demonstrated with GCI of 2.3%. The validation domain spans the full clinical CPB operating envelope. The structured evidence chain from foundational experimental data through code verification, discretization error quantification, and output comparison supports the conclusion that the model is fit for the intended purpose of identifying worst-case hemolysis conditions for regulatory submission of the Class II CPB device.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
